                            }
                        ],
                        "text": "The torcheater sharply inhales to consume a source of light within its reach, such as a torch's flame, a *light* spell, or another effect no larger than a human. It automatically extinguishes a non-magical flame, and it attempts to counteract a magical fire or light effect at 2nd-rank with a counteract modifier of +8. If the torcheater successfully counteracts an effect, it gains a reach of 10 feet, a +5 foot status bonus to Speed, and fast healing 2 until the end of its next turn, plus an additional number of rounds equal to the counteracted effect's rank. During this time, the creature's body solidifies, reducing its resistance to physical damage to 2.  \n  \n The torcheater can spend two actions to instead affect a light source it can perceive within 30 feet."
                    }
